    "The specific values of λ n r = α n are referred to as the zeros of the Bessel function J 0 [9] and are used to determine the shape of the drum that determines the frequency with which it vibrates, as shown in Figure 2.D H (r, t) = ∞ n=1 J 0 (λ n r) * (A cos(c d λ n t)+B sin(c d λ n t)) (3)In this work, we utilize drumhead vibration to compute the source frequency (human or ChatGPT) (E f0) for the computation of observed frequency by an observer (human) in the Doppler effect.",
